AMERICAN WINES

American Wines are coming of age. Each one listed here can hold its head high against the wines of Europe, except possibly for the famed giants of France and Germany. Here are the great growers of America who are dedicated to making good wine. We particularly single out the excellent wines grown and bottled in the Sonoma Valley by Samuele Sebastiani, whose wines are favorites among Californians and are now being introduced for the first time to the wine-drinkers of New York.
